The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, April 30, 2004 				 Death and drama off Bengal train 
																								Bhadrak, April 29 (PTI): Police arrested a 35-year-old man who caused panic at the station here by stabbing to death one person, injuring another and taking the guard of a train hostage. 																								Shabir Khan, whose identity is yet to be established, quarrelled with a man at the station and stabbed him, police said. 																								Apparently, all three  the victim, the injured man and the killer  had travelled here by Dhauli Express, which had just arrived from Howrah. 																								After the murder, the assailant jumped into the guards cabin and took him hostage. He demanded that the train should leave. 																								Khan surrendered after negotiations and was arrested. The knife was seized from him and he is being interrogated. 																								The train, stranded at the station for over three hours, left for Bhubaneswar at 1.45 pm.
